imdb.title: Ueki no hôsoku
imdb.plot: A young student named Kousuke Ueki gets chosen to battle in a tournament. Kousuke has the power to turn garbage into trees and will fight against other students.

episodes.title: Ueki kôsuke seigi no hôsoku
episodes.plot: Kosuke Ueki is a Power User with the ability to change trash into trees, a gift bestowed by his king candidate Kobayashi. He fights in a tournament against other Power Users to decide the next King of the Celestial World.

episodes.title: Batoru kaishi!! no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki befriends Seiichiro Sano who can turn towels into steel, then battles Mauro Taira, who can turn water into fire.

episodes.title: Zai no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki fights Toshio Asachi, who can change cotton into stakes.

episodes.title: Taijutsu no otoko, Rihou no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki fights Li Ho, who prefers to use his own martial arts skills to fight rather than his power.

episodes.title: Saraba no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki takes on Robert Haydn, the strongest Power User who can manipulate gravity using his bubbles. Robert is too strong for Ueki and prepares for the killing blow.

episodes.title: Kobasen no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki searches for answers in Mr. K's home and takes on Bolo T, who can change his forehead into diamond.

episodes.title: Seisei doudou! Onimon no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki fights the fair minded Onimon, who can turn the dirt he kicks into cannonballs.

episodes.title: Onimon no tokugun no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki fights Black Shadow, who can turn shadows into clay men.

episodes.title: Mukuwarenu seigi no housoku
episodes.plot: Black Shadow reveals the injustice he suffered in the past that lead to him joining the Robert's Ten.

episodes.title: Roberuto juudan no housoku
episodes.plot: Now that Ueki has beaten White Shadow, a member of the Robert's Ten, he is invited to join them.

episodes.title: Tenkaijin no housoku
episodes.plot: Mori and Mr. K discover that Ueki was actually a heavenly being sent to Earth as a baby. Meanwhile Ueki turns on Alessio Juliano, who can turn dirt into scythes.

episodes.title: Tenkaijuu no housoku
episodes.plot: Just when Ueki and Alessio's fight gets started, a celestial beast called Tenko erupts from the ground.

episodes.title: Kakusei zouki no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki is no match for Don, who can change a ring into a rocket.

episodes.title: Rinko no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki is challenged by two Power Users: Marco Maldini who can turn tomatoes into magma and Rinko Jerrard who can turn beads into bombs.

episodes.title: Neo no housoku
episodes.plot: Tenko and Rinko give Ueki some time to heal, fighting off Ogre who can turn a bamboo sword into hedge clippers, Becky Wolf who can turn BB bullets into meteorites, and Taro Myojin who can turn whistles into laser beams.

episodes.title: Futatsu no chikara no housoku
episodes.plot: Myojin reveals himself as a cheater, having been illegally granted 2 powers: to turn whistles into laser beams and to turn cards into saws.

episodes.title: Senritsu! Doguramanshion no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki is invited to a party hosted by Robert Haydn and fights Yunpao, a power user with the ability to turn electricity into sugar.

episodes.title: Kosakku Dansu no housoku
episodes.plot: Despite having no powers, Mori fights Kabara, who can turn a cape into wings.

episodes.title: Sano Seiichiro no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki is up against Seiichiro Sano, the Power User he was trying to save.

episodes.title: Inumaru no housoku
episodes.plot: It is revealed that Sano joined the Robert's Ten to rescue Inumaru, who must now make a courageous sacrifice.

episodes.title: Ueki VS Juudan no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki takes on Carpaccio, who can copy other people's powers, including all of the Robert's Ten.

episodes.title: Shonen Roberuto no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki has his rematch with Robert and gets an insight into Robert's tragic past.

episodes.title: Fukkatsu! Kobasen no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki finds himself losing to Robert, whose Level 2 Power makes him invincible.

episodes.title: Kyoufu! Anon no housoku
episodes.plot: Round One of the tournament ceases, while a new villain rises to replace Robert.

episodes.title: Hideyoshi no hôsoku
episodes.plot: For the upcoming team tournament, Ueki and Mori try to recruit a Power User by the name of Hideyoshi Soya who can change his voice into a portrait.

episodes.title: Taiyô no ie no hôsoku
episodes.plot: The Caption Team wants to destroy the House of the Sun so that Hideyoshi won't have a reason not to join them anymore.

episodes.title: Shinanai de tenko no hôsoku
episodes.plot: Tenko has a secret: if he raises Ueki to nine stars, Tenko will die.

episodes.title: Sanji senkô no hôsoku
episodes.plot: Ueki's Team heads to the celestial world where they meet four rival Power User teams. Ueki's Team's first match is against the Grano Team.

episodes.title: Saikyô taggu no hôsoku
episodes.plot: Sano and Rinko have a tag team battle against Munin who can turn puns into reality, and Pastello who can turn a drawing into a portal.

episodes.title: Hontô no tsuyosa! no hôsoku
episodes.plot: Pecol decides to quit working with Grano. With the ability to turn models into real objects, Grano summons a giant robot to combat Ueki.

episodes.title: Gekitotsu! Ueki VS Rihou no housoku
episodes.plot: Li Ho questions Ueki's ability to defeat Team Marilyn.

episodes.title: Maririn Chiimu no housoku
episodes.plot: Team Ueki is unprepared against Team Marilyn's military experience and coordinated plans.

episodes.title: Hakattanaaaaaa! no housoku
episodes.plot: Baron blocks Ueki with his power to teleport to wherever his knife is.

episodes.title: Nakama no shoumei no housoku
episodes.plot: Sano, Mori, and Hideyoshi face the remaining members of Team Marilyn.

episodes.title: Jinki no jyakuten no housoku
episodes.plot: Proving that his sacred weapons aren't as weak as others think, Ueki returns to save his team.

episodes.title: Sano, kakusei!! no housoku
episodes.plot: Sano is left to face Matthew, who can turn his arms into six arms. Soon his Level 2 Power awakens.

episodes.title: Tozasareta kororo no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki struggles against Marilyn's ability to turn one second into ten seconds, and discovers secrets about her tragic past.

episodes.title: Subarashii 'Ai' no housoku
episodes.plot: Mori faces Memory, despite not knowing what her power even is.

episodes.title: Honmono to nisemono no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki meets his biological father.

episodes.title: Barou chiimu no housoku
episodes.plot: Rinko goes first and realizes that Team Barrow is composed entirely of celestials sent to support Hanon.

episodes.title: Burikko poozu no housoku
episodes.plot: After Sano and Diegostar's battle ends, Mori takes on Kill Norton with her situational power.

episodes.title: Ueki, reberu 2! no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki removes his celestial powers so he can master his Level 2 Power, but unfortunately must battle Barrow, who can change an image from the past into current reality.

episodes.title: Kako kara no kougeki no housoku
episodes.plot: Ueki has finally attained his Level 2 Power to revert the powers of others back to their original forms.

episodes.title: Kami to shoujo to mirai no housoku
episodes.plot: The King tells his story of the girl who inspired him, Haruko Ueki.

episodes.title: Kami ni natta Anon no housoku
episodes.plot: Hanon swallows the King and changes the rules of round four.

episodes.title: Daiyonji senkoku no housoku
episodes.plot: The fourth round begins, the rules being that the first to defeat Hanon will win.

episodes.title: Juutsu hoshi no housoku
episodes.plot: Team Ueki and Team Barrow team up against Hanon.

episodes.title: Ueki vs Anon no housoku
episodes.plot: The final battle between Ueki and Hanon begins as Archenemy, the tenth sacred weapon is finally revealed.

episodes.title: Kuuhaku no zai no housoku
episodes.plot: Because Ueki only has eighteen talents left, he only has eighteen chances to defeat Hanon. At the end of the tournament, the final victor will claim the Talent of Blank.
